Style instruction:
{% if style == "black_white_drawing" -%}
Transform the image into a black and white hand-drawn illustration. Use pencil or ink linework, natural shading, subtle cross-hatching, and paper texture. Keep the result like a detailed observational drawing, not a cheap filter and not a cartoon.
{% elif style == "watercolor" -%}
Transform the image into a soft watercolor study. Use translucent pigment, paper grain, gentle color bleeding, loose edges, and muted natural tones. Keep the memory recognizable, just rendered as watercolor.
{% elif style == "animated" -%}
Transform the image into a clean animated illustration style. Use simplified shapes, smooth clean outlines, expressive but natural colors, soft lighting, and a polished animated-film look. Keep it warm and personal, not childish or overly exaggerated.
{% endif %}

Intensity instruction:
{% if intensity == "subtle" -%}
Keep the transformation subtle and close to the original feeling. Avoid extreme changes.
{% elif intensity == "balanced" -%}
Balance realism and artistic interpretation. Make the mood clear without overdoing it.
{% elif intensity == "expressive" -%}
Push the emotion more strongly with bolder lighting, color, atmosphere, and symbolism while keeping the memory recognizable.
{% endif %}

